	<name>AOSC Media Writer</name>
	<summary>A tool to create a live USB drive with an edition of AOSC</summary>
	<description>
		<p>A tool to create a bootable live USB drive with an edition of AOSC. Not only can AOSC Media Writer write an image to your flash drive, it can also download it for you. It offers official editions (Server, Workstation), AOSC spins (KDE Plasma Desktop, Xfce Desktop, Cinnamon Desktop,...), and AOSC Labs (Design Suite, Security Lab,...). It provides basic information about each of them to help you make the right choice.</p>
		<p>AOSC Media Writer can also write other bootable ISOs loaded from your local disk, but keep in mind that it's only tested with AOSC images.</p>
	</description>
